Sriram Nambakam (11):
  Introduce VM Plane support with KVM
  Activate the planes configuration - allocate resources for each plane
    - initialize planes in KVM
  Iterate through each plane (id > 0) and load the kernel. - wait till
    all the vCPUs associated with that plane halt
  enable hypercalls related to vm planes
  vm_planes: fix plane vCPU initialization and memory model
  Remove comments specific to CONFIG_SMP - the kernel in plane 1 could
    be build with CONFIG_SMP=y
  vm_planes: Add VBS VTL call handling and plane memory sealing
  vm_planes: Implement VBS SEAL_KERNEL and PROTECT_MEMORY dispatchers
  vm_planes: Add module authentication handlers for VBS VTL calls
  vm_planes: Add kexec validation and invalidation VBS handlers
  update definition for KVM_CAP_VM_PLANES - match definition in kernel

